race.comment: JARMON (2) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at Shepparton over 390m behind Foxy Jay (22.98) in a Grade 5. Has ability and looks hard to stop. MATCHBOX HONEY (5) was out of the placings last time when eighth at Healesville (20.27) but scored four back at Warragul (26.52). Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Leading chance. MCIVOR MORGAN (1) won again in an impressive display after enjoying a good run to make it back to back wins, scoring at this track over 500m (28.75). In great form and can continue his winning ways. MORNING DAISY (8) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.
